lation</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">State</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Label</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lts</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Semantics/LTS/Basic.html#Cslib.LTS\">LTS</a> <span class=\"fn\">State</span> <span class=\"fn\">Label</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">State</span> → <span class=\"fn\">State</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A relation is a simulation if, whenever it relates two states in an lts,\nany transition originating from the first state is mimicked by a transition from the second state\nand the reached derivatives are themselves related. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Foundations/Semantics/LTS/Simulation.html#Cslib.Simulation","kind":"def","line":51,"name":"Cslib.Simulation","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/7f88669e78c0fa9d9c4f41a397072114cbb9aa7e/Cslib/Foundations/Semantics/LTS/Simulation.lean#L51-L55"}}],"imports":["Init","Cslib.Foundations.Semantics.LTS.Basic"],"instances":[{"className":"Trans","name":"Cslib.instTransSimulationEquiv","typeNames":["Cslib.SimulationEquiv","Cslib.SimulationEquiv","Cslib.SimulationEquiv"]}],"name":"Cslib.Foundations.Semantics.LTS.Simulation"}